.TH lpjrun 1  "USER COMMANDS"
.SH NAME
lpjrun \- Run parallel LPJmL program interactively.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lpjrun
[-hostfile \fIhosts.list\fP] ntasks [args ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Script runs LPJmL simulation in parallel invoking the
.B mpirun
command.  Has been tested on Apple MacOS X and Ubuntu.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
-hostfile \fIhosts.list\fP
Distribute tasks on hosts specified in the \fIhosts.list\fP file. The number of entries in \fIhosts.list\fP must be at least the number of task specified.
.TP
ntasks
Set the number of parallel MPI tasks.
.TP
args
Set command line arguments for the
.B lpjml
program.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run program with 8 parallel MPI tasks starting from a restart file:
.B lpjrun
8 -DFROM_RESTART lpjml_config.cjson
.PP
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
LPJROOT
defines the root directory for LPJmL. The variable has to be defined before calling
.B lpjrun
.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.B lpjrun
returns a zero exit status if LPJmL run fails.
Non zero is returned in case of failure.

